rate adjustment should be modest.\n\nRevised estimate from base rate: **+8-12 percentage points** due to political climate, but significant friction remains.\n\n## (g) Community prediction and divergence explanation\n\nI do not have access to current Metaculus community predictions for this specific question. However, given the question's focus on concrete government action with a defined deadline, I would expect community forecasters to be similarly cautious, likely in the 10-25% range.\n\nMy probability reflects:\n- Recognition of shifted political environment (supports higher estimate)\n- Absence of specific legislative vehicles or state proposals (supports lower estimate)\n- Short 7-month implementation window (supports lower estimate)\n- Historical precedent strongly against such programs (supports lower estimate)\n- Complexity of establishing new government programs (supports lower estimate)\n\n---\n\n## Final Reasoning\n\nThis question requires actual implementation of a new government program with specific features (monetary rewards, civilian eligibility, formal establishment) within 7 months. While the Trump-aligned Republican political environment has created conditions more favorable to immigration enforcement, the actual translation of rhetoric into enacted law with full bureaucratic implementation has proven slower than partisan rhetoric suggests.\n\nThe absence of any serious legislative proposal or state-level initiative currently (as of June 2026) is notable. Even with unified Republican control, substantive immigration legislation has faced delays and political constraints. Implementation would require appropriations, administrative infrastructure, legal review, and operational setup\u2014realistically a 4-6 month minimum process after enactment.\n\nThe resolution criteria require the program to be \"active\" before January 1, 2027\u2014meaning operational, not merely proposed or passed. This raises the bar significantly.\n\nBalancing the favorable political climate against practical implementation barriers and historical precedent:\n\n**Probability: 18%**",
